{
  "texts": [
    "A variety of sensing devices may be used to conduct the initial clinical assessment virtually at home, and subsequently collect physiological, ambient, and contextual data from patients at home during VRehab sessions 8.",
    "For instance, a webcam/camera on a personal computer or smartphone can be used to capture videos of patients while performing rehabilitation exercises which could provide important information on their functional recovery.",
    "A smartwatch with a built-in accelerometer can provide vital data on mobility parameters, including the number of steps taken and sedentary lifestyle 35, 36.",
    "These single or multi-modal data can be used to build AI algorithms for measuring patients' overall improvements in their rehabilitation program and providing feedback, resources, and encouraging notifications to patients to complete their programs successfully.",
    "AI algorithms using sensor data to make inferences about various patient health outcomes can be classified into three main approaches: end-to-end, feature-based, and hybrid 10."
  ]
}